    "description": "Fabrica Holdings Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the business communication activities in Japan. It operates through Business Communication Business, Automotive Platform Business, AI Business, and Auto Service Business segments. The company offers communication platforms comprising Media short message service (SMS), an SMS delivery system; TeleForce, an AI-powered interactive voice response (IVR) service; and Action Link, a CRM system specialized for e-commerce businesses. It also provides automotive platforms consisting of symphony, an automobile sales support system for car dealers; Quicar, a cloud-based vehicle inspection and maintenance billing system; and Truck Bank, a truck sales media solution. In addition, the company offers automobile accident repair and vehicle inspection; and body repair and paint services. Further, it engages in business support system development and sales; SMS distribution solution; internet media; web marketing; automobile maintenance and rental car; and blockchain and AI related businesses, as well as sale of new and used cars through online; operation of online automobile magazines; and used car appraisal services. The company was formerly known as Fabrica Communications Co., LTD. and changed its name to Fabrica Holdings Co., Ltd. in April 2024. Fabrica Holdings Co., Ltd. was founded in 1992 and is headquartered in Minato, Japan."
